name: Godinho Bar and Restaurant

reviews.review_text:
Chance bought us here. Upon walking in Panjim, we came across this place. Don't judge a book by it's cover...

A lovely place, we were fortunate to get a table even thou we just walked in, noticed that after a short while of our arrival they received many patrons.

On that unusually hot day , we were not really hungry for a full meal. Beer, a plate of fries, Chicken lolipop and Chicken Xacuti was ordered. Food was delicious, service was quick and efficient.

Noticed, who I'm guessing is the owner, was walking around to the tables and making sure the patrons received their orders and were happy. No one walked up to us thou. Nonetheless, my parents were content.

Something that struck me was, when the bill arrived there was no taxes mentioned, guessing it must be added to their menu instead.

Overall was a good experience in Panjim. A must visit. You should try some of the local food they have and also their drinks.

Godinho's was on our bucket list for a while, and it definitely lived up to its reputation. The place has a warm, cozy vibe with a great ambiance that makes you feel right at home. The food is excellent, and I highly recommend exploring the prawns dishes.

The overall experience was fantastic. Whether you're going there for a meal or just for drinks, the quality and flavors are on point. If you're a football fan, you'll love the café's decor, which features posters and paintings celebrating the sport. It's a nice touch that adds to the overall charm of the place. If you're in the area, Godinho's Café is definitely worth a visit!

It's like a cozy little haunt you'd come to for a quick pint after work. We had a pomfret fish curry, a king fish rawa fry and roasted pork. Roasted pork was an excellent accompaniment to the drinks we had. On that note, do ask the price of the seasonal fish before you place an order!

description:
### A Taste of Goa: Godinho Bar and Restaurant

Nestled in the vibrant streets of Panjim, Godinho Bar and Restaurant has captivated diners with an impressive rating of 4.2 stars from 804 reviews. This beloved establishment is a cherished spot for both locals and tourists, boasting popular dishes such as **beef steak**, **squid**, and the traditional **xacuti**, reflecting its Portuguese culinary roots.

### Ambiance & Design

As you step into Godinho’s, you are greeted by a warm and cozy ambiance that invites you to relax and unwind. The décor showcases a charming café vibe, enriched by football-themed art that adds a lively touch for sports enthusiasts. The lighting is perfect—soft yet enough to illuminate the details of the restaurant's inviting setup. Reviewers have expressed their affection for the overall atmosphere, likening it to a cozy haunt ideal for a casual meet or a post-work pint. Images of the bar show a blend of rustic and modern design, creating an inviting space that feels like a home away from home.

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The menu at Godinho Bar and Restaurant is a delectable representation of both local Goan and Portuguese cuisine. Signature dishes include the **pomfret fish curry**, **king fish rawa fry**, and, of course, the much-praised **Chicken Xacuti**. Each dish is presented with care—vibrant colors and tantalizing aromas that promise a gastronomic delight. The food consistently receives high praise, with customers noting the exceptional flavor and freshness of every bite. For those seeking lighter fare, the menu offers a variety of local delicacies and shrimp dishes that have also garnered rave reviews. Vegetarians will find options to suit their preferences as well.

### Customer Experience & Service

Customer service at Godinho is a hallmark of its success, characterized by a friendly and efficient team who ensure a pleasant dining experience. Reviewers have observed the owner's attentive nature, as they often mingle with guests to guarantee satisfaction. While some patrons mentioned the lack of continual check-ins, the overall sentiment is one of appreciation for the service quality. Guests have noted that the restaurant accommodates both walk-ins and reservations, making it accessible for spontaneous visits or planned meals with friends and family.

### Popularity & Reviews

Godinho Bar and Restaurant’s reputation has made it a must-visit when in Goa. Diners frequently comment on the vibrant atmosphere and excellent food, while social media chatter and glowing reviews suggest it rightly holds a place of honor on many travelers' itineraries. The establishment has also secured its spot on various food guides, often highlighted for its authentic Goan experience.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The imagery shared by guests beautifully complements the restaurant's narrative. Photos reveal a bustling bar scene filled with warmth and camaraderie, while food images display beautifully plated dishes that not only satisfy the palate but also delight the eyes. From the vibrant curries to the rustic décor, each snap captures a unique facet of Godinho’s charm, inviting even more patrons to step through its doors.

### Conclusion

In summary, Godinho Bar and Restaurant is a delightful gem in Panjim's culinary landscape. With its strong ratings, cozy ambiance, and delectable menu, it promises an experience that celebrates the richness of Goan and Portuguese cuisine. Whether you’re a foodie seeking authentic local flavors or just looking for a place to unwind with a cold drink and good company, Godinho’s ensures a memorable dining experience that lingers long after the last bite. Don’t miss the chance to savor their local specialties and enjoy the warm hospitality that keeps patrons returning for more.
